          <h1>Kids Have Hope, a Chicago Non-Profit Organization</h1>
          <h2>
            Kids Have Hope is a 501c3 nonprofit organization dedicated to 
            preventing child physical abuse and sexual abuse through 
            empowerment and education.
          </h2>
          <h3>What We Do</h3>
          <p>
            Kids Have Hope provides an evidence-based curriculum 
            on prevention and awareness of child sexual abuse including; 
            sexual abuse, emotional abuse, physical abuse, violence 
            prevention and bullying. We provide this service to students 
            in  pre-school through 6th grade.
          </p>
          <p>
            We offer educational in-services to schools and 
            communities which help prevent and detect child sexual 
            abuse by raising awareness and implementing effective 
            strategies.  Our information sessions are designed for 
            teachers, faculty, parents, health care providers and 
            community members who want to prevent and detect child 
            sexual abuse.
          </p>
          <h3>Request Professional Assistance</h3>
          <p>
            We are available to answer questions about child abuse or 
            you can setup a meeting with one of our Licensed Social 
            Workers who can explain, in detail, our various programs.
            Contact us for an initial meeting and take a stand to stop child 
            sexual abuse.
          </p>
        </section>
